00157    virtual void Visit(const PDI::DisplayElement& string) {
00158       std::istringstream ss(string);
00159 
00160       char cPeekCharacter = ss.peek();
00161 
00162       if (cPeekCharacter == '&')
00163       {
00164          // This is either a StaticType usage or a DynamicType usage:
00165          // "NameStaticTypeUsage" : "&Alias Size"
00166          // "NameDynamicTypeUsage" : "&Alias($Variable) Size"
00167 
00168          // Split the stream into two different tokens defined by a space between them.  The second one is size.
00169          std::string sAlias;
00170          std::string sSize;
00171          ss >> sAlias >> sSize;
00172 
00173          // The following code does this...
00174          //1) Determine if this is a static or dynamic usage by looking for the (
00175          //2) If this is static, then create an AliasedInstruction and pass in the nSize, sAlias.
00176          //3) If this is dynamic, then
00177          //3a) Split Alias into two strings (one being &Alias and the other being $Variable, and strip off the parenthesis)
00178          //3b) Create an AliasedInstruction and pass in the nSize, sAlias, $Variable.
00179 
00180          size_t nLocationOfOpenParen = sAlias.find('(');
00181          size_t nLocationOfCloseParen = sAlias.find(')');
00182                    if ((nLocationOfOpenParen != std::string::npos) & (nLocationOfCloseParen != std::string::npos))
00183          {
00184             // This is a dynamic Aliased Instruction (It has a parameter).
00185             std::string sVariable = sAlias.substr(nLocationOfOpenParen+1, nLocationOfCloseParen-nLocationOfOpenParen-1);
00186             sAlias = sAlias.substr(0, nLocationOfOpenParen);
00187                         m_pInstruction = new BabelShark::AliasedInstruction(sSize, m_sName, sAlias, sVariable);
00188          }
00189          else
00190          {
00191             // This is a static Aliased Instruction (It does not have a parameter).
00192             m_pInstruction = new BabelShark::AliasedInstruction(sSize, m_sName, sAlias);
00193          }
00194 
00195       }
00196       else
00197       {
00198          // This is a Simple Display Element in one of the following layouts:
00199          // "NameSimple" : "Type Size"
00200          // "NameSimple" : "Type Size $Optional_Variable"
00201 
00202          std::string sType;
00203          std::string sSize;
00204          std::string sVariableName;
00205          ss >> sType >> sSize >> sVariableName;
00206 
00207          CreateInstructionFuncMap::const_iterator it = m_CreateInstructionFuncMap.find(sType);
00208          if (it == m_CreateInstructionFuncMap.end())
00209          {
00210             std::string sException = "use of undefined type: " + sType;
00211             throw std::exception(sException.c_str());
00212          }
00213          else
00214          {
00215             if (m_bDisplayOutputToScreen)
00216             {
00217                std::cout << "This leaf node has been visited " << m_sName << " " << sType << " " << sSize << " " << sVariableName << std::endl;
00218             }
00219          }
00220 
00221          CreateInstructionFunc func = it->second;
00222          m_pInstruction = (this->*func)(sSize, m_sName, sVariableName);
00223       }
00224    }
